The week in 37 photos

Published 6:43 PM EDT, Thu June 5, 2025
Link Copied!

A 45-year-old Egyptian national has been charged with a federal hate crime after an attack left at least 12 people injured in Boulder, Colorado, on Sunday.

According to charging documents, suspect Mohamed Sabry Soliman used a homemade flamethrower and Molotov cocktails to attack demonstrators who were at a peaceful Jewish event supporting hostages in Gaza. He later told authorities that he wanted to kill all Zionist people and wished they were all dead, an affidavit said.

Soliman had been planning the assault for a full year, he told federal authorities. He also faces state charges of attempted murder.

Soliman appeared in state court Monday and was expected to appear in federal court on Friday. CNN has reached out to his attorney for comment.

Soliman, his wife and their five children arrived in the United States in 2022. The White House said Tuesday that the familys deportation was imminent, but a federal judge ordered a halt to that on Wednesday.

Here are some of the stories that made headlines over the past week, as well as some photos that caught our eye.

Editor's note: This gallery contains a disturbing image. Viewer discretion is advised.

Mount Etna can be seen erupting near Catania, Italy, on Monday, June 2. Although Mount Etna is one of the worlds most active volcanoes, there hasnt been an eruption of this magnitude since 2014, according to the National Institute of Geophysics and Volcanology Observatory.
Five-year-old Osama al-Raqab, suffering from severe malnutrition, undergoes treatment at the Nasser Hospital in Khan Younis, Gaza, on Saturday, May 31. Israel halted all humanitarian aid into Gaza in early March, with government officials saying their goal was to force Hamas to accept new ceasefire terms and release hostages taken during the militant groups terror attack on Israel on October 7, 2023. The ban meant no supplies entered the territory for 11 weeks, pushing Gazas 2.1 million people deeper into a hunger crisis. Israel eased its blockade two weeks ago, allowing a small amount of aid to enter Gaza, but the amount of aid trickling in is nowhere near enough to meet the needs of the population, according to Palestinian officials and international aid groups.
A man takes a nap next to a tennis court in Paris during the French Open on Thursday, May 29.
A bat is captured for research by a scientist from the Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute in Gamboa, Panama, on Sunday, June 1.
This satellite image, taken on Wednesday, June 4, shows destroyed aircraft at an air base in Russias Irkutsk region. Ukrainian forces destroyed dozens of Russian warplanes parked at air bases thousands of miles from the front lines, according to a source in the countrys security services.
A blacksmith sharpens knives at a shop in Karachi, Pakistan, ahead of the Muslim festival of Eid al-Adha on Thursday, June 5.
New South Korean President Lee Jae-myung bows at the conclusion of his inauguration ceremony in Seoul on Wednesday, June 4.
Members of the US Army Parachute Team jump from a plane during training in Maxton, North Carolina, on Wednesday, June 4.
A boy pulls on the reins of two camels at the Birqash camel market on the outskirts of Giza, Egypt, on Wednesday, June 4.
Climate activist Greta Thunberg is photographed in Catania, Italy, on Saturday, May 31, a day before she and 11 other activists set sail for Gaza. Their ship was going to try to reach the shores of Gaza to bring in some aid and raise international awareness over the ongoing humanitarian crisis, the activists said at a news conference.
A person takes part in the annual LGBTQ+ Pride parade in Bangkok, Thailand, on Sunday, June 1.
The Edmonton Oilers Leon Draisaitl, right, scores in overtime to lift his team to a 4-3 victory over Florida in Game 1 of the NHLs Stanley Cup Final on Wednesday, June 4. The same two teams played in last years final. Florida came out on top.
A Ukrainian serviceman observes the sky during an overnight shift in Ukraines Kharkiv region on Sunday, June 1.
A boy sleeps on sacks of garbage along the polluted Pasig River in Manila, Philippines, on Thursday, June 5.
The Milky Way galaxy can be seen from Californias Death Valley National Park on Thursday, May 29.
A donkey is led past a polling station as a man votes in San Bartolom Quialana, Mexico, on Sunday, June 1. Mexicos ruling party Morena will gain control of the Supreme Court following the countrys first-ever judicial elections, which were marred by low voter turnout and allegations of a power grab.
Paris Saint-Germain midfielder Dsir Dou celebrates after scoring in the Champions League final against Inter Milan on Saturday, May 31. PSG thrashed the Italian side 5-0 to win the tournament for the first time in its history. Dou scored two goals and was named Man of the Match.
Young friends Elliott Clark and Gwen Pfeifer ride a mini Ferris wheel at the Good Neighbor Days festival in Washington, DC, on Friday, May 30.
A man walks his dogs as wildfire smoke billows near Highway 97, north of Buckinghorse River, British Columbia, on Friday, May 30. Massive wildfires in western and central Canada forced thousands to flee and sent hazardous smoke toward major cities in the United States.
Kansas outfielder Tommy Barth slams into the outfield wall as he makes a catch during an NCAA regional in Fayetteville, Arkansas, on Friday, May 30.
A Muslim pilgrim prays while overlooking the Kaaba, Islam's holiest shrine, at the Grand Mosque complex in Mecca, Saudi Arabia, on Monday, June 2.
Ballroom dancers take part in a monthly Tea Dance in the Great Hall of the Rochdale Town Hall in Rochdale, England, on Wednesday, June 4. Tea dances are social events that combine the traditions of afternoon tea and dancing. They originated in the 1880s.
Fans are reflected in glass as Gael Monfils serves during a French Open match in Paris on Thursday, May 29.
Wild horses run in the Merfelder Bruch near Dlmen, Germany, on Saturday, May 31.
Thick smoke and flames erupt from an Israeli airstrike in Gaza City on Sunday, June 1.
Romanias Denisa Golgot performs on the uneven bars during the European Artistic Gymnastics Championships on Thursday, May 29.
A worker cleans the lines of a cooling tower at an ice factory in Karachi, Pakistan, on Thursday, May 29.
Ryan Blaney celebrates with a burnout after he won the NASCAR Cup Series race at the Nashville Superspeedway in Tennessee on Sunday, June 1.
Montpellier's Thomas Vincent, left, and Racing 92's Max Spring jump to catch the ball during a rugby match in Nanterre, France, on Saturday, May 31.
The peak of Annapurna Is north face is seen from Myagdi, Nepal, on Monday, June 2.
People in Sutamarchn, Colombia, throw tomatoes during the annual Gran Tomatina festival on Sunday, June 1.
A stork and two chicks nest on a high-voltage line mast in Boue, France, on Tuesday, June 3.
A carpenter works after a power outage in Tehran, Iran, on Sunday, June 1.
Greek army helicopters take part in a US-led military exercise in Petrochori, Greece, on Wednesday, June 4.
Dance school students wait outside Romania's Palace of Parliament during a series of events marking International Children's Day in Bucharest, Romania, on Sunday, June 1.
Alpacas chill on a meadow on the outskirts of Innsbruck, Austria, on Friday, May 30. See last week in 38 photos.
